#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn17.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Dīghalomikasutta → dīghalomieḷakasuttaṃ (bj) | dīghalomi (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn17.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Dīghalomikasutta "
msgstr "4. A Fleecy Sheep "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn17.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.4:1.2"
msgid "“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya. "
msgstr "“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.4:1.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dīghalomikā eḷakā kaṇṭakagahanaṃ paviseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose a fleecy sheep was to enter a briar patch. "

# NOTE: BB has “here and there”, but the idiom is different. “Here and there “means” in some places”. tatra tatra is distributive, it means “everywhere, you can’t escape it”.
#. VAR: gayheyya → gaccheyya (si) | gaṇheyya (s1-3, km, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn17.4:1.4"
msgid "Sā tatra tatra sajjeyya, tatra tatra gayheyya, tatra tatra bajjheyya, tatra tatra anayabyasanaṃ āpajjeyya. "
msgstr "She’d get caught, snagged, and trapped at every turn, coming to ruin. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.4:1.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, idhekacco bhikkhu lābhasakkārasilokena abhibhūto pariyādiṇṇacitto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati. "
msgstr "In the same way, take a certain mendicant whose mind is overcome and overwhelmed by possessions, honor, and popularity. They robe up in the morning and, taking their bowl and robe, enter the village or town for alms. "

msgctxt "sn17.4:1.6"
msgid "So tatra tatra sajjati, tatra tatra gayhati, tatra tatra bajjhati, tatra tatra anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "They get caught, snagged, and trapped at every turn, coming to ruin. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.4:1.7"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … "
msgstr "So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …” "

msgctxt "sn17.4:1.8"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.4:1.9"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

